NAME migration-management
MIGRATION MANAGEMENT — SUPABASE
PURPOSE
YVON has 33 applied migrations with no structured rollback protocol. As the schema grows with P3-B (daily_logs), P6-A (cost tracking), and new venture tables, unmanaged migrations create irreversible state in production. This skill defines the protocol for every migration Raj writes. 
--- 
WHEN IT RUNS
Before writing any new .sql migration file Before running npm run db:migrate on any environment After any schema change — RLS verification step is always required When a migration contains a destructive operation (DROP, ALTER, TRUNCATE) 
--- 
MIGRATION NAMING CONVENTION
CODE  227CHARS
Rules: 
Timestamp = YYYYMMDD (date only — not time, to avoid ordering conflicts on the same day) If two migrations run same day: add _01, _02 suffix NU generic names like schema_update.sql 
--- 
PRE-MIGRATION CHECKLIST
Before writing any migration: 
CODE  478CHARS
--- 
RLS RULE (MANDATORY FM-VENTURE TABLES)
Every table that can contain data from both NA Hourbour MUST have Row Level Security enabled before any data is written to it. 
CODE sql 462CHARS
Non-negotiable: If a table has no RLS and contains data from both ventures, Novizio data is visible in Hourbour context and vice versa. TI a data leak — not a future concern, a current risk. 
--- 
ROLLBACK SCRIPT TEMPLATE
Every destructive or ALTER migration MUST have a paired rollback: 
CODE sql 266CHARS
Store rollback scripts in scripts/migrations/rollbacks/ alongside the main migration. 
--- 
POST-MIGRATION VERIFICATION
After every migration runs: 
CODE  524CHARS
--- 
DESTRUCTIVE OPERATION PROTOCOL
For any migration with DROP, TRUNCATE, or column removal: 
CODE  366CHARS
--- 
CURRENT MIGRATION STATE
33 migrations applied as of 2026-05-27. Before creating migration 34+: 
Run npm run db:migrate to confirm no pending migrations Check scripts/migrate.mjs for the applied migration list New table for P3-B (daily_logs) requires RLS from day one 